PROJECT PHILOSOPHY

OptikR is a community-driven, open-source project built with the following values:

FREEDOM & ACCESSIBILITY
- Free to use for any purpose (personal, educational, commercial)
- No paywalls, no subscriptions, no artificial limits
- Source code available for learning and improvement
- Community contributions welcome and encouraged

TRANSPARENCY
- All code is open and auditable
- Development process is transparent
- Issues and fixes are documented
- Community feedback shapes the project

ATTRIBUTION
- If you use OptikR in your project, a mention would be appreciated (but not required)
- If you improve OptikR, consider contributing back to help others
- Share your dictionaries, plugins, and translations with the community

COMMUNITY FIRST
- Built by the community, for the community
- No corporate ownership or control
- User needs come first, not profit
- Everyone can contribute, regardless of skill level

================================================================================

WHAT THIS MEANS FOR YOU

✅ You CAN:
- Use OptikR for free, forever
- Use it for personal projects
- Use it for commercial projects
- Modify the code for your needs
- Distribute your modified versions
- Create plugins and extensions
- Share dictionaries and translations
- Learn from the code
- Fork the project

✅ You DON'T HAVE TO:
- Pay anything
- Ask for permission
- Provide attribution (but it's appreciated!)
- Share your modifications (but it helps the community!)
- Contribute back (but we'd love it if you do!)

⚠️ You SHOULD:
- Respect the licenses of third-party components (see below)
- Be a good community member
- Help others when you can
- Report bugs and suggest improvements
- Share your improvements if possible

❌ You CANNOT:
- Remove copyright notices
- Claim you created OptikR
- Hold the authors liable for any issues

